\details{
An \link[mlr3:LearnerClassif]{mlr3::LearnerClassif} that fits a Guided Regularized Random Forest (GRRF)
for use in \link[mlr3filters:mlr_filters_importance]{mlr3filters::FilterImportance}-based feature selection.

The learner implements a two-stage approach:
\enumerate{
\item An initial unregularized random forest estimates variable importance scores.
\item Those scores are normalized and used to compute per-feature split-selection
weights (\code{coefReg}), penalizing less informative predictors.
\item A second "guided regularized" forest is trained with those weights, and its
impurity importance scores are exposed via \verb{$importance()}.
}

Class-balanced sample weights are computed automatically from the target column,
so no external weight vector is required.
}
\section{Parameters}{

\itemize{
\item \code{gamma} (\code{numeric [0, 1]}, default \code{0.5}): Guidance coefficient.
\code{0} = unguided regularized forest (equal penalty for all features);
\code{1} = strongest guiding effect (most important features penalized least).
\item \code{num.trees} (\code{integer >= 1}, default \code{500}): Number of trees in each forest.
\item \code{max.depth} (\code{integer >= 0}, default \code{100}): Maximum tree depth (\code{0} = unlimited).
}
}

